On the other: McKinsey=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CAI Agentic Mesh=E2=80=9D (distrib=
uted autonomous agents, grounded in=E2=80=A6 PowerPoint slides lol)
Fun aside, this isn=E2=80=99t just another framework war=E2=80=94it=E2=80=
=99s a perfect case study in how the same technology gets interpreted compl=
etely differently depending on whether you=E2=80=99re building or consultin=
g. It=E2=80=99s been really fun to dive into this one because the stakes ar=
e real. We=E2=80=99re watching billions get allocated based on these compet=
ing visions, and only one of them is going to survive contact with reality.
Here=E2=80=99s the thing: I normally keep the deep strategic breakdowns beh=
ind the paywall, but this battle felt too important to gate. Consider this =
a taste of what subscribers get every week=E2=80=94the kind of analysis tha=
t cuts through the noise and shows you what=E2=80=99s actually happening.
Because while executives are choosing sides, there=E2=80=99s real transform=
ation happening in the quiet corners where developers are shipping with AI.
So let=E2=80=99s roll up our sleeves and dig in. You=E2=80=99ll get:
The real story behind both visions
Why the communication gap between builders and executives keeps creating ex=
